definition: gold/chemical element Au/generic term for lustrous and ductile metals/money/golden/highly respected/one of the eight categories of ancient musical instruments 八音[ba1 yin1]

sentences.english: He was motivated by the hope of fathering a male heir to the Tudor Dynasty.
sentences.chinese: 他這樣做是爲了都鐸王朝能有一名男性繼承人。

sentences.english: Check out the Tudor tatler for the inside scoop on all the news that was fit to print.
sentences.chinese: 翻看都鐸新聞報紙，可以找到適於付版的內部消息。
英國在都鐸王朝時代處於全盛期。

sentences.english: Metal skins will be welded together with lasers, eliminating thousands of fasteners.
sentences.chinese: 金屬外殼由激光鐸成一體，從而免去成千上萬個扣釘。

sentences.english: He assured me that it still works, and he takes it to Tok every now and then.
sentences.chinese: 他向我保證，它仍然有效，他考慮到鐸已經開始。

sentences.english: The Tudor Dynasty was founded after the Hundred Years War and the Rose War.
sentences.chinese: 都鐸王朝處在英法百年戰爭和紅白玫瑰戰爭結束之後。

sentences.english: Tudor Court represents your opportunity to locate at the heart of the new Birmingham.
sentences.chinese: 都鐸宛，您在新伯明翰中心區置業的好機會。

sentences.english: Pork was the main meat of the peasant in Tudor times.
sentences.chinese: 在英國都鐸王朝時期，豬肉是農村主要的肉類來源。

sentences.english: The political tradition of Tudor dynasty determines its low rate of financial support.
sentences.chinese: 英國的政治傳統，決定了都鐸王朝較低的財政供養率。

sentences.english: Elizabeth I was the last of the Tudors.
sentences.chinese: 伊利莎白一世是都鐸王朝的最後一個君主。

sentences.english: Prayer necessarily occupies a central place in the life of the Priest.
sentences.chinese: 祈禱無可或缺地佔據鐸職生活的中央位置。

sentences.english: Admiration for the drawings of Watteau has always been equal to that of his paintings.
sentences.chinese: 人們對華鐸繪畫的讚賞總是與他的畫作相互同等。

sentences.english: The rebuilding of the nave was begun by 1376 and continued intermittently until Tudor times.
sentences.chinese: 中堂於1376年開始改建，間斷地持續至都鐸時代。
